# Master Development Rules

## 🚨 Critical Project-Specific Rules

### 1. Database → Prisma Only (Never Supabase .from())

```typescript
// ✅ ALWAYS
const data = await prisma.keyType.findMany({ where: { userId } });

// ❌ NEVER
const { data } = await supabase.from('KeyType')...
```

### 2. Auth → getCurrentUser() with Multi-Organisation Support

```typescript
// Standard pattern used in ALL server actions
import { getCurrentUser } from '@/lib/auth-utils';

// Returns: { id, email, activeOrganisationId, roleInActiveOrg, allOrganisations[] }
const user = await getCurrentUser();

// Use activeOrganisationId for data filtering
const keys = await prisma.keyType.findMany({
  where: { entityId: user.activeOrganisationId },
});
```

### 3. UI → shadcn/ui + Tabler Icons + ResponsiveDialog

```typescript
// ❌ NEVER plain HTML
<button>Click</button>

// ✅ ALWAYS use shadcn/ui + Tabler Icons
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { IconPlus } from '@tabler/icons-react';

<Button><IconPlus className="h-4 w-4" />Add</Button>

// ✅ Use ResponsiveDialog for user-facing dialogs (auto mobile/desktop)
import { ResponsiveDialog } from '@/components/ui/responsive-dialog';

<ResponsiveDialog
  open={isOpen}
  onOpenChange={setIsOpen}
  title="Dialog Title"
  footer={<Button>Save</Button>}
>
  <div>Content</div>
</ResponsiveDialog>
```

### 4. Server Actions → Standard Result Type

```typescript
'use server';
type ActionResult<T> = { success: true; data?: T } | { success: false; error: string };

export async function action(formData: FormData): Promise<ActionResult<any>> {
  try {
    const userId = await getCurrentUserId();
    // Always filter by userId for data isolation
    const result = await prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
      // Multi-step operations in transactions
    });
    revalidatePath('/path');
    return { success: true, data: result };
  } catch (error) {
    return { success: false, error: 'Operation failed' };
  }
}
```

### 5. Data Isolation → Always Filter by activeOrganisationId

```typescript
const user = await getCurrentUser();

// ✅ ALWAYS filter by activeOrganisationId for multi-tenant isolation
where: { entityId: user.activeOrganisationId, ...otherConditions }

// ❌ NEVER query without organisation filter (security risk)
where: { id } // Missing entityId filter!
```

### 6. Documentation → Only in docs/ Directory

- ✅ `docs/security/`, `docs/development/`, `docs/product/`
- ❌ NEVER create `.md` files in project root (except README.md)

## 📊 Project Schema (Quick Reference)

```typescript
User { id, email (unique), activeOrganisationId? }
UserOrganisation { userId, organisationId, role, joinedAt }
Entity { id, name, encryptionKey } // "Organisation" in UI
KeyType { label, function, entityId }
KeyCopy { copyNumber, status, keyTypeId }
Borrower { name, email, entityId }
IssueRecord { issuedDate, returnedDate?, keyCopyId, borrowerId, userId }

// User can belong to multiple organisations (via UserOrganisation)
// activeOrganisationId tracks which org user is currently working in
```

